https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500null Sequences of frames, sampled from a Big Brother broadcast on Channel 4 television, are repeated three times each in rhythmic succession. Nothing is slowed down or speeded up, but movement becomes unreal and fractured, parts of spoken words tumble out into a new stream of image and sound, and “reality television” begins to look like Pop Art. Dominant Culture
